modules.description: Provides compile-time validation for SPARQL queries through custom syntax extensions. Includes core types for representing query structures and operations for parsing and checking query validity. Users can embed SPARQL queries directly in OCaml code and ensure syntactic correctness before runtime. Example: verifying SELECT ?x WHERE { ?x a ?y } is valid during compilation.

Provides functions to create, query, and manipulate RDF graphs using SPARQL queries. Works with data types such as triples, graphs, and SPARQL query structures. Enables tasks like extracting specific subject-predicate-object relationships and executing filtered queries on semantic data.

Injects SPARQL query validation into OCaml compilation, using custom syntax to check query structure and ensure correctness at build time. Defines core types for query components and provides parsing functions to enforce syntax rules. Allows users to embed and validate queries like SELECT ?x WHERE { ?x a ?y } directly in code. Supports early error detection by integrating validation into the OCaml toolchain.
